{
  "text": ". Given the normalization of the fading channels and the additive noise in our channel model, in (2) may be interpreted as an SNR per receive antenna. Since the channel defined in (1) is i.i.d., we may drop the time index in the sequel for convenience. The sender and receiver can interactively communicate over the discussion channel between each successive use of the channel. We refer to the reader to [CITATION_1] for a formal description of the protocol. Furthermore, we are interested in the secret-key capacity between the sender and the receiver. We again refer to the reader to [CITATION_2] for a formal description and definition of key capacity.",
